On April 9 in France, the Agence Française de Développement launched “COVID-19 – Health in Common” – a €1.2 billion initiative in response to the worldwide public health crisis caused by the COVID-19 pandemic." The initiative is the result of a collaboration between the French President and his African peers and prioritizes "the 19 priority countries for French aid in Africa, the ocean basins (Madagascar, Comoros and Haiti) and the Middle East. 

The main objectives of the initiative are the following:
(1) Reinforcing regional epidemiological surveillance networks;
(2) Contributing to national COVID-19 response plans in African countries;
(3) Supporting the main French actors in the response to COVID-19 (NGOs, foundations, networks, research bodies, etc.);
(4) Providing budget support for the reinforcement of healthcare systems.
